                           <tr>
                              <td class="starter" valign="top">attribute</td>
                              <td class="starter" valign="top">The attribute is used to describe a attribute of an objectClass.<para/>You can define a attribute value either by giving the value to a property named <emphasis role="bold">classname</emphasis>:<emphasis role="bold">attributename</emphasis> to an object, or by using a model structure defined by the defaults of the given attribute.</td>
                           </tr>
                           <tr>
                              <td> </td>
                              <td/>
                           </tr>
                           <tr>
                              <td class="starter" valign="top">def</td>
                              <td class="starter" valign="top">The id of a default related to the attribute.<para/>The property is represented by a tag named 'type' in the policy file.</td>
                           </tr>
                           <tr>
                              <td> </td>
                              <td>
                                 <table class="propertytable">
                                    <tr>
                                       <td>attribute:type</td>
                                       <td>xs:string</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
